  <messages>
    <message id="m0000" time="2010-08-24 19:12:24 UTC" participant="153901">
      <body>isn't "charming condescension" an oxymoron?</body>
    </message>
    <message id="m0001" time="2010-08-24 19:18:21 UTC" participant="153902">
      <body>Not necessarily.</body>
    </message>
    <message id="m0002" time="2010-08-24 19:18:56 UTC" participant="153902">
      <body>Condescension is a characteristic exhibited by one person</body>
    </message>
    <message id="m0003" time="2010-08-24 19:19:09 UTC" participant="153902">
      <body>Charming is a subjective qualification by another</body>
    </message>
    <message id="m0004" time="2010-08-24 19:20:28 UTC" participant="153901">
      <body>I don't know whether to be flattered or insulted</body>
    </message>
    <message id="m0005" time="2010-08-24 19:21:01 UTC" participant="153901">
      <body>So you don't think that condescension is subjective?</body>
    </message>
    <message id="m0006" time="2010-08-24 19:22:20 UTC" participant="153902">
      <body>Of course it's subjective, but on the speaker's part, not the audience</body>
    </message>
    <message id="m0007" time="2010-08-24 19:22:45 UTC" participant="153902">
      <body>Charming is the audience's subjective interpretation</body>
    </message>
    <message id="m0008" time="2010-08-24 19:22:49 UTC" participant="153901">
      <body>so you can choose to be condescending?</body>
    </message>
    <message id="m0009" time="2010-08-24 19:23:02 UTC" participant="153902">
      <body>Yes</body>
    </message>
    <message id="m0010" time="2010-08-24 19:23:06 UTC" participant="153901">
      <body>but you cannot choose to be charming</body>
    </message>
    <message id="m0011" time="2010-08-24 19:23:14 UTC" participant="153902">
      <body>You can attempt to be charming</body>
    </message>
    <message id="m0012" time="2010-08-24 19:23:30 UTC" participant="153902">
      <body>But the audience determines whether you succeed</body>
    </message>
    <message id="m0013" time="2010-08-24 19:23:33 UTC" participant="153901">
      <body>but can't intent and interpretation be different?</body>
    </message>
    <message id="m0014" time="2010-08-24 19:23:35 UTC" participant="153902">
      <body>Which is not the case with condescenion</body>
    </message>
    <message id="m0015" time="2010-08-24 19:23:40 UTC" participant="153902">
      <body>Yes</body>
    </message>
    <message id="m0016" time="2010-08-24 19:24:04 UTC" participant="153901">
      <body>so I may not be trying to be condescending, but could be interpreted that way</body>
    </message>
    <message id="m0017" time="2010-08-24 19:24:13 UTC" participant="153902">
      <body>Well, that's always the case</body>
    </message>
    <message id="m0018" time="2010-08-24 19:24:46 UTC" participant="153902">
      <body>People can take whatever you say however they want</body>
    </message>
    <message id="m0019" time="2010-08-24 19:24:46 UTC" participant="153901">
      <body>But if I am received as charming, I was more than likely my goal</body>
    </message>
    <message id="m0020" time="2010-08-24 19:25:01 UTC" participant="153902">
      <body>Maybe</body>
    </message>
    <message id="m0021" time="2010-08-24 19:25:05 UTC" participant="153901">
      <body>they can, but they can also take it the wrong way</body>
    </message>
    <message id="m0022" time="2010-08-24 19:25:10 UTC" participant="153902">
      <body>Yes.</body>
    </message>
    <message id="m0023" time="2010-08-24 19:25:36 UTC" participant="153902">
      <body>That's why clear communication and awareness of language is important! ^_^</body>
    </message>
    <message id="m0024" time="2010-08-24 19:25:53 UTC" participant="153901">
      <body>especially via IM</body>
    </message>
    <message id="m0025" time="2010-08-24 19:25:57 UTC" participant="153901">
      <body>=|</body>
    </message>
    <message id="m0026" time="2010-08-24 19:26:22 UTC" participant="153902">
      <body>Yup</body>
    </message>
    <message id="m0027" time="2010-08-24 19:26:39 UTC" participant="153901">
      <body>do you think I am condescending?</body>
    </message>
    <message id="m0028" time="2010-08-24 19:26:58 UTC" participant="153901">
      <body>and I am not asking this solely based on your comment last night</body>
    </message>
    <message id="m0029" time="2010-08-24 19:27:23 UTC" participant="153902">
      <body>I think a better question would be whether I think condescension is a negative or offensive trait.</body>
    </message>
    <message id="m0030" time="2010-08-24 19:27:52 UTC" participant="153901">
      <body>that may be a better question, but not the one that I asked</body>
    </message>
    <message id="m0031" time="2010-08-24 19:28:06 UTC" participant="153902">
      <body>You can come across as condescending sometimes.</body>
    </message>
    <message id="m0032" time="2010-08-24 19:28:21 UTC" participant="153902">
      <body>But I don't find it particularly offensive.</body>
    </message>
    <message id="m0033" time="2010-08-24 19:28:31 UTC" participant="153901">
      <body>well, thank you</body>
    </message>
    <message id="m0034" time="2010-08-24 19:28:36 UTC" participant="153901">
      <body>I think..,</body>
    </message>
    <message id="m0035" time="2010-08-24 19:28:37 UTC" participant="153902">
      <body>I usually consider it a symptom of intelligence. /shrug</body>
    </message>
    <message id="m0036" time="2010-08-24 19:28:52 UTC" participant="153901">
      <body>indeed</body>
    </message>
    <message id="m0037" time="2010-08-24 19:28:55 UTC" participant="153902">
      <body>I'm sure I come across as condescending or dismissive sometimes.</body>
    </message>
    <message id="m0038" time="2010-08-24 19:29:09 UTC" participant="153901">
      <body>"Is there nowhere for the man with 105 I.Q.?"</body>
    </message>
    <message id="m0039" time="2010-08-24 19:29:16 UTC" participant="153902">
      <body>Not in my life</body>
    </message>
    <message id="m0040" time="2010-08-24 19:29:26 UTC" participant="153901">
      <body>I quote Homer Simpson</body>
    </message>
    <message id="m0041" time="2010-08-24 19:31:47 UTC" participant="153901">
      <body>I think that generally speaking condescension is not viewed as a positive trait.</body>
    </message>
    <message id="m0042" time="2010-08-24 19:32:08 UTC" participant="153901">
      <body>Especially by people with low self-esteem</body>
    </message>
    <message id="m0043" time="2010-08-24 19:32:21 UTC" participant="153902">
      <body>That's because they want someone to hold their hand and think happy thoughts with them.</body>
    </message>
    <message id="m0044" time="2010-08-24 19:32:31 UTC" participant="153901">
      <body>true</body>
    </message>
    <message id="m0045" time="2010-08-24 19:32:40 UTC" participant="153901">
      <body>those people drive me crazy</body>
    </message>
    <message id="m0046" time="2010-08-24 19:33:43 UTC" participant="153901">
      <body>I do not intend to be condescending, but due to my dry, sarcastic sense of humor and my somewhat thick-headed honestly I feel that it is sometimes unavoidable</body>
    </message>
    <message id="m0047" time="2010-08-24 19:34:01 UTC" participant="153901">
      <body>*honesty</body>
    </message>
    <message id="m0048" time="2010-08-24 19:34:20 UTC" participant="153902">
      <body>Yes</body>
    </message>
    <message id="m0049" time="2010-08-24 19:34:32 UTC" participant="153902">
      <body>That's why it doesn't bother me. /shrug</body>
    </message>
    <message id="m0050" time="2010-08-24 19:34:48 UTC" participant="153901">
      <body>I like that</body>
    </message>
    <message id="m0051" time="2010-08-24 19:34:50 UTC" participant="153902">
      <body>It's more of a rhetorical effect than a judgement.</body>
    </message>
    <message id="m0052" time="2010-08-24 19:35:17 UTC" participant="153901">
      <body>It takes a bit more than that to offend me</body>
    </message>
    <message id="m0053" time="2010-08-24 19:35:49 UTC" participant="153901">
      <body>The reason I asked is because this is the second time in just over a week that I was accused of being condescending</body>
    </message>
    <message id="m0054" time="2010-08-24 19:35:59 UTC" participant="153902">
      <body>http://onefte.com/2010/05/27/if-only/</body>
    </message>
    <message id="m0055" time="2010-08-24 19:37:39 UTC" participant="153901">
      <body>that would make a great poster</body>
    </message>
    <message id="m0056" time="2010-08-24 19:37:52 UTC" participant="153902">
      <body>I have it taped up in my cube</body>
    </message>
    <message id="m0057" time="2010-08-24 19:38:07 UTC" participant="153902">
      <body>I hide it though</body>
    </message>
    <message id="m0058" time="2010-08-24 19:38:20 UTC" participant="153902">
      <body>So as to not offend people of inappropriate I.Q.s</body>
    </message>
    <message id="m0059" time="2010-08-24 19:38:33 UTC" participant="153901">
      <body>right, don't want to seem condescending</body>
    </message>
    <message id="m0060" time="2010-08-24 19:39:20 UTC" participant="153902">
      <body>http://onefte.com/2010/08/20/</body>
    </message>
    <message id="m0061" time="2010-08-24 19:39:24 UTC" participant="153901">
      <body>weird...it's not really socially acceptable to make fun of stupid people...or fat people</body>
    </message>
    <message id="m0062" time="2010-08-24 19:39:27 UTC" participant="153902">
      <body>Probably my current favorite</body>
    </message>
    <message id="m0063" time="2010-08-24 19:39:50 UTC" participant="153902">
      <body>It is, however, perfectly acceptable to demonize and condescend to people due to their intelligence.</body>
    </message>
    <message id="m0064" time="2010-08-24 19:39:57 UTC" participant="153902">
      <body>Our culture is pretty fucked up</body>
    </message>
    <message id="m0065" time="2010-08-24 19:40:28 UTC" participant="153901">
      <body>explain</body>
    </message>
    <message id="m0066" time="2010-08-24 19:41:35 UTC" participant="153901">
      <body>and in many ways, it does make sense.  We don't get to choose how smart we are</body>
    </message>
    <message id="m0067" time="2010-08-24 19:41:53 UTC" participant="153902">
      <body>Some people are not capable of thinking clearly.</body>
    </message>
    <message id="m0068" time="2010-08-24 19:42:00 UTC" participant="153902">
      <body>Some people choose not to try.</body>
    </message>
    <message id="m0069" time="2010-08-24 19:42:53 UTC" participant="153901">
      <body>but that may also have to do with their ability</body>
    </message>
    <message id="m0070" time="2010-08-24 19:44:07 UTC" participant="153901">
      <body>I know I can be cocky at times, but what is the alternative?  Be bashful and unsure of myself</body>
    </message>
    <message id="m0071" time="2010-08-24 19:44:28 UTC" participant="153902">
      <body>The alternative is to stop listening or caring about what idiots think.</body>
    </message>
    <message id="m0072" time="2010-08-24 19:44:46 UTC" participant="153901">
      <body>I once scolded and ex for apologizing too much, and she then said she was sorry</body>
    </message>
    <message id="m0073" time="2010-08-24 19:45:12 UTC" participant="153901">
      <body>she apologized for apologizing too much =|</body>
    </message>
    <message id="m0074" time="2010-08-24 19:45:44 UTC" participant="153901">
      <body>I don't care what they think, but I can't stop listening to it</body>
